DPRK FM Blasts Japan's Adoption of "Amendment to Law on Foreign Exchange" 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 30 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the DPRK Foreign Ministry issued a statement today, denouncing the House of Representatives of Japan for passing the "amendment to the law on foreign exchange" through the Diet on Jan. 29.
 The amendment stipulates that the remittance to the DPRK and trade with it shall be stopped when necessary and that Japan shall apply sanctions against the DPRK single-handed without any UN resolution or any international agreement under the pretext of "ensuring peace and security of Japan". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Dismissing this as a wanton violation of the DPRK-Japan Pyongyang Declaration in which both sides committed themselves to observe international law and not to do any act of threatening the security of the other side, the statement continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 World history never knows such an untrustworthy country as Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was only 16 months ago that Japan requested for Koreans' forgiveness, saying that "the Japanese side admitted, in a spirit of humility, facts of history that Japan caused tremendous damage and sufferings to the Korean people through its colonial rule in the past and expressed deep remorse and heartfelt apology." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 However, it is now set to apply sanctions against the country that fell victim to it in the past with a dagger in hand. How can one understand this in a normal way of thinking although the Japanese-style ethics is so crafty? &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is pushing the DPRK-Japan relations to an unpredictable phase by legislating on economic sanctions against the DPRK as a state policy. 
 Its move will not be confined to this. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This development will bring peace and stability in Northeast Asia to a catastrophic phase and further deteriorate the situation on the Korean peninsula that has grown tense due to the nuclear issue between the DPRK and the US. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The government and the ruling camp of Japan are expecting someone to make any concession, prattling that the adoption of this bill "would deal an unimaginable economic and psychological blow at north Korea". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan, however, is so foolish as to make such a serious miscalculation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has always considered its sovereignty as its life and soul throughout its history and does not know any precedent of abandoning its principle, yielding to others' pressure or allowing itself to be a slave. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If Japan expects the DPRK to cave in to the threat of such a war criminal state as Japan, everybody will have a good laugh over it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As Japan sows so shall it reap. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will not remain a passive onlooker to Japans act of seriously infringing upon its sovereignty and putting Tokyo's hostile policy into practice through economic sanctions and blockade while talking about its participation in the six-way talks, but take necessary counter-measures against it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the DPRK's mettle to return retaliation for retaliation and react against the hard-line policy with the toughest measure. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan will be wholly responsible for all consequences to be entailed by its foolish moves.

Ugandan National Preparatory Committee Formed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 30 (KCNA) -- An inaugural ceremony of the Ugandan National Preparatory Committee for Commemorating the Day of the Sun and February 16, birthday of leader Kim Jong Il, was held in Kampala on January 19.
 Present at the ceremony were Minister of State for Water, Lands and Environment of Uganda Baguma Isoke, Senior Adviser to the Presidency Chango Machyo and other political and public figures and members of the Juche idea study groups and organizations for friendship and solidarity with the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the ceremony the minister of State for Water, Lands and Environment was elected chairman of the preparatory committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The committee decided to conduct activities in different forms and ways for introducing the greatness of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il and supporting the just cause of the Korean people on the occasion of the Day of the Sun and February 16. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A message of greetings to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the ceremony.

Double-Dealing Tactics Can Never Work on DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 30 (KCNA) -- The U.S. administration is reported to have contended recently that the nuclear issue between the U.S. and the DPRK should be solved peacefully and diplomatically.
 While advocating a diplomatic and peaceful solution to the nuclear issue, the U.S., however, let loose a string of provocative remarks that the "nuclear crisis in north Korea is an issue that might be referred to the UN Security Council and it might prompt the SC to discuss the possibility of sanctions against it" and "Washington hoped that north Korea would solve the crisis over its nuclear program diplomatically." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In this regard Rodong Sinmun today in a signed commentary says it is nothing but a base ruse to twist the nature of the issue that the U.S. is asserting the DPRK-U.S. nuclear issue remains unsolved due to the DPRK's fault. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The nuclear issue between them is a direct product of the U.S. hostile policy toward the DPRK. It deteriorated as the United States threatened the DPRK, a non-nuclear state, with nukes and attempted to mount a preemptive nuclear attack on it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 However, the U.S. has delayed and obstructed the solution to the issue, insisting on its assertion that "the DPRK should abandon its nuclear program first". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the U.S. truly stands for a peaceful solution to the nuclear issue, it should not insist on its unreasonable assertion but accept the DPRK-proposed package solution based on the principle of simultaneous actions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Whether the U.S. accepts the DPRK proposal or not is a touchstone showing whether it hopes for the peaceful solution to the nuclear issue or not. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The United States should drop its double-dealing tactics and take an honest approach.

GNP Shows Signs of Ruin
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 30 (KCNA) -- One more scandal of the Grand National Party of south Korea has been brought to light some days ago. So Chong Won, former representative of the GNP, obtained a housing bond worth 1 billion won directly from the chairman of the Han Hwa Group.
 Now the GNP has no face to raise its head any longer and is seeking a loophole, says Rodong Sinmun today in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is high time the GNP politicians dropped ultra-right conservative ideas and such bad habits as extorting truck-loads of money, though they are left behind in civilization and enlightenment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Dismayed at the truth of illicit funds disclosed more glaringly day by day from the outset of the year, the GNP clan vociferated again about the outdated "theory of political coloring" and cried out for a "constitutional reform" and "hearing on presidential election funds" all of a sudden. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The GNP is at the point of death for which it is entirely to blame. This situation was a result of its anti-popular policy, treacheries and sycophantic and submissive behavior. Such being a stark fact, the GNP politicians are well advised to understand their position and behave themselves with conscience before the public and the people, if they have an iota of reason. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But Hong Sa Dok, chief for General Affairs of the GNP, hurled a string of vituperation at the chief executive's side in a bid to divert to it the public criticism focused on the party. Not content with this, he, a few days ago, went to the lengths of making reckless remarks that the "foolish people" wrongly chose the president at the last presidential election. This caused such a furor that "petitions" were submitted to accuse him. This indicates that the GNP's fate is at stake and this traitorous party has shown signs of ruin. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 From a historic and organizational point of view the GNP has no way to go any further and it is bound to go to doom for its crimes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The GNP's destruction is unavoidable.

KCNA Warns against Japan's Moves for Overseas Aggression
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 30 (KCNA) -- The Japanese reactionaries are now getting into full stride in their moves for overseas aggression, oblivious of the lesson of history.
 No sooner had the Japanese chief executive expressed his willingness on January 26 to dispatch a main unit of the "Self-defence Forces" to Iraq following an advance unit than Defense Agency Chief Ishiba ordered the main unit to Iraq. This gave the green light to military operations of a large unit of the SDF equipped with such heavy weapons as armored vehicles, recoilless artillery pieces and portable anti-tank bombs in combat areas overseas as a shock brigade of the U.S. forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This means that the Japanese reactionaries have shaken off the veil of the "UN peace-keeping operations" they had been wearing and opened up a prelude to overseas aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries' dispatch of the SDF combat troops to Iraq was prompted by their shrewd intention to give a helping hand to the U.S. in its awkward position and earn profits in the division of interests including oil. Another important aim sought by them in the troop dispatch is to build a framework for turning Japan into a military giant and militarizing it and secure a justification for overseas aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese authorities are now driving the Japanese society to the Right with all speed by whitewashing Japan's past history of aggression, paying visits to the "Yasukuni Shrine" and spreading ultra-nationalism while establishing the Missile Defense System, launching spy satellites and trying to have access to nuclear weapons in a bid to emerge a military power at an early date. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Very disturbing developments brought to Japan today by the Japanese right-wing forces remind one of the eve of Japan's aggression of Korea and Asian continent in the past century and this indicates that the Japanese reactionaries' ambitious moves to militarize the country and turn it into a military power for reinvasion have been adopted as a state policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What remains to be done by them now is to work out a war constitution whereby to mobilize all human and material resources as the final step to the completion of their preparations for a war of overseas aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In last November the Japanese chief executive openly called for revising the constitution and elevating the status of the SDF to Defense Ministry. And Secretary General of the Liberal Democratic Party Abe in his Fuji TV appearance on Jan. 8 cried for exercising right to collective self-defence and revising the constitution. All these were part of the attempts to remove the last roadblock in the way of reinvasion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a well-known fact that Japan has so far gnawed away little by little at Article 9 of the present constitution which bans the possession of a regular army and war by adopting "law on emergency," "law related to Japan-U.S. defence cooperation guidelines" and "law on anti-terrorism." But it is the first time for the chief executive and heavyweights of the ruling party to openly call for the exercise of right to collective self-defence and the revision of the constitution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is as clear as noonday that once the Japanese society got militarized and turned into a military power such fascist elements as Tojo would appear on the scene and launch reinvasion, holding sway over the Japanese politicaldom &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korea and other Asian countries are not what they were in the past when they were trampled underfoot and plundered by the Japanese imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries will never be able to evade a miserable lot if they keep pushing for militarization to become a military power.

Meeting of Officials in Charge of Party Ideological Work to Be Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 30 (KCNA) -- A meeting of officials in charge of the ideological work of the Workers' Party of Korea will be held in Pyongyang in late February.
 The meeting will bring together officials who have contributed to firmly arming Party members and other working people with the revolutionary idea of the WPK and powerfully arousing them to the socialist construction, while faithfully working in this field for years, true to the idea and leadership of the Party and the leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It will review with pride the great achievements and experience gained in the work to model the whole society on the Juche idea under the leadership of the WPK and discuss tasks to be fulfilled to intensify the ideological work of the Party as required by the Songun era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting will mark a historic occasion in praising the immortal exploits the WPK has performed by leading the revolution and construction along the road of victory indicated by the Juche idea, guided by the theory of ideology, fully demonstrating the singlehearted unity of the whole Party, all the servicepersons and people in thinking and purpose and laying another milestone in accelerating the building of a great prosperous powerful nation with the might of the Songun idea.

Setting Period of Congratulating Sun of 21st Century Called for
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 30 (KCNA) -- An appeal was published in Lima on Jan. 20 by the Latin American and Caribbean Regional Committee to Support the Reunification of Korea, the General Kim Jong Il Peruvian Amicable Institute, the Peruvian-Korean Institute of Friendship and Culture and the Peruvian Committee for Supporting the Independent and Peaceful Reunification of Korea with the birthday of leader Kim Jong Il approaching.
 The appeal recalled that two years ago a "meeting of congratulating the sun of the 21st century" was held on a grand scale in Mt.Paektu as an international political and cultural function on the occasion of the birthday of Kim Jong Il and decided to hold him in high esteem as the great sun leading the human cause of independence to victory in the new century and adopted the Mt. Paektu Declaration proclaiming it to the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that this was a historical event of great significance in accomplishing the human cause of independence, it called upon all the progressives, international organs, international democratic organizations and organizations for friendship and solidarity with the Korean people: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Let us sing more widely "Song of General Kim Jong Il" as a paean of whole humankind as urged in the Mt. Peaktu Declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Let us set the days from February to April every year as a "period of congratulating the sun of the 21st century" and conduct diverse political and cultural events in a peculiar manner in the period. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Let us make it a regular function to visit the native home in the secret camp in Mt. Peaktu of Korea, the holy land of the sun, in every five year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Let us vigorously wage on the global scale the movement for support to and solidarity with the Korean people in their just cause of defending socialism and achieving the independent and peaceful reunification of the country, upholding the great Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will continue to energetically conduct activities to unswervingly carry forward the spirit of the Mt. Paektu Declaration reflecting the desire of the world progressives to have Kim Jong Il possessed of peculiar political ability and traits of a great man as the sun of the 21st century.

Meeting of Officials in Field of Agriculture Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 30 (KCNA) -- A national meeting of officials in the field of agriculture was held in Pyongyang on Jan. 28.
 A report by Ri Kyong Sik, minister of Agriculture, was followed by speeches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter and speakers referred to the fact that last year the officials and other working people in the field of agriculture worked hard to implement the policy of the Workers' Party of Korea on bringing about a signal turn in agriculture despite unfavorable natural and climatic conditions, the land realignment projects made rapid progress in various areas including Pyongyang,Nampho and South Phyongan Province and valuable experience was accumulated in the potato-farming and double cropping. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They stressed the need to make a leap forward in the agricultural production in this historic year that will witness unforgettable events such as the 40th anniversary of the publication of President Kim Il Sung's work "Theses on the Socialist Rural Question in Our Country". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Pak Pong Ju, premier of the Cabinet, and members of the Cabinet and officials concerned.

Meeting of Officials in Field of Land and Environmental Protection Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 30 (KCNA) -- A meeting of officials in the field of land and environmental protection was held in Pyongyang on Thursday.
 A report by Jang Il Son, minister of Land and Environmental Protection, was followed by speeches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter and speakers said that servicepersons and working people, true to leader Kim Jong Il's plan for land construction, have successfully carried out the yearly assignments for land administration through a mass movement though they were hard pressed for everything. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Calling for bringing about a revolutionary turn in the work to give face-lifting to the land of the country so that it may befit the land of a great prosperous powerful nation this year, a significant year in the nation's history, they underscored the need for all officials and other working people to successfully honour this year's plan for land administration and thus make the land look more beautiful. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Pak Pong Ju, premier of the Cabinet, Jong Ha Chol, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, and Cabinet members, senior officials of the ministries, central organs and working people's organizations, senior officials of provincial, city and county party, power and economic institutions, officials in the field of land and environmental protection and the related fields.

National Symposium Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 30 (KCNA) -- A national symposium of historians was held at Kim Il Sung University Thursday to mark the 30th anniversary of President Kim Il Sung's instructions to excavate Tomb of King Tongmyong.
 Prof. and Dr. Jong Chi Gon, dean of a faculty of the university, Dr. Son Su Ho, director of an institute of the Academy of Social Sciences, and Dr. Song Sun Thak, deputy curator of the Korean Central History Museum, made speeches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They noted that the questions surrounding the Tomb of King Tongmyong were solved scientifically from the Juche-oriented stand and it was splendidly rebuilt as a historic monument of national treasure illustrating the history and cultural tradition of powerful Koguryo on the principle of historicism thanks to the noble patriotism of Kim Il Sung and his tireless and energetic leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The tomb of King Tongmyong, who left indelible footprints in the history of the nation, is a precious historical monument and treasure indicative of the history and cultural tradition of Korea together with the mausoleum of King Tangun, the ancestral father of the Korean nation, and the tomb of King Wang Gon, founder king of Koryo, the first unified state of Korea, in view of its style symbolizing Koguryo, its scale demonstrating the absolute power of the monarch of a powerful state and its location befitting that of the father of a legitimate state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They cited quotations from a series of documents and archeological data and gave descriptions of the socio-historical background of Koguryo to scientifically prove that the tomb in Ryongsan-ri, Ryokpho District, Pyongyang is that of the founder king of Koguryo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Koguryo not only succeeded Tangun Korea and orchestrated the history in the period of Three Kingdoms but had a great influence on the development of history of successive states that appeared in Korea thereafter ranging from Palhae, Koryo to Ri Dynasty, they said, concluding that Koguryo was a country which led the main stream of the history of the Korean nation in the middle age. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The symposium was attended by Thae Hyong Chol, president of the Academy of Social Sciences, officials concerned, university presidents and college rectors, and history researchers.

Kimjongilia Festival in Preparation
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 30 (KCNA) -- Preparations for the 8th Kimjongilia Festival to be held in Pyongyang on the occasion of the auspicious February holiday, birthday of Kim Jong Il, are active across the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 Brisk preparations are being made by the ministries and national institutions including the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces, the Ministry of People's Security, the Ministry of Posts and Telecommunications and the Ministry of Culture which won visitors' estimation in past festivals. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Academy of Sciences and the Ministry of Railways are doing their best to bring Kimjongilia into full bloom for the festival. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
They are paying deep attention to controlling the temperature, light and humidity in their greenhouses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kimjongilia is coming into bloom in several hundred Kimilsungia and Kimjongilia greenhouses built in all the provinces, cities and counties amid deep concern and expectation of the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean Kimilsungia and Kimjongilia Committee has instituted the flag of the Kimjongilia Festival and is touching a finishing hand to the preparations to sponsor the festival successfully. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The scale of the festival and the number of its participants have ever increased since its first festival was held in Juche 86 (1997). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The forthcoming festival is expected to be participated in by more units and individuals at home, overseas Koreans and florists and amateurs of various countries.

Best Option: Death-defying Fight against U.S.
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 30 (KCNA) -- The first secretary of the Central Committee of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League and the chairperson of the Central Committee of the Korean Democratic Women's Union issued statements on Jan. 29 in support of the appeal of the joint meeting of the DPRK government, political parties and organizations.
 They said the five-point tasks and proposals to build the structure of Korean nation-U.S. confrontation by practical actions and pave a wide avenue for independent reunification, upholding the Korean nation-first spirit as the common banner of the nation, are a very just and timely measure. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The most correct option and only way to defend the dignity and sovereignty of the country and the nation is a death-defying fight against the U.S., they declared. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 First Secretary Kim Kyong Ho said the youth and students of the DPRK would be ardent patriots in defending Songun politics, leaving their destiny and future to it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chairperson Pak Sun Hui stated that all the women would vigorously turn out in the just and patriotic sacred struggle to pave a wide avenue for independent reunification in close solidarity with all women in south Korea and overseas.
